other_tests.changes_over_time: At 10 months, the ECG stress test was again positive for myocardial ischemia.

other_tests.findings: Severe atherosclerosis in 2 vessels; 95% stenosis in the mid portion of the right coronary artery with 75% stenosis at the crux and 95% stenosis in the proximal portion of the left anterior descending coronary artery.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Nine months later, there was restenosis in the paclitaxel-eluting stent in the proximal left anterior descending coronary artery, treated with a rapamycin-eluting stent.
